The paper proposes a framework for discovering options in reinforcement learning, which involves building a model of the state space using Successor Representations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also applies the proposed framework to robotic control environments, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of high-dimensional spaces and grid-worlds, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
